President Obama attended a meeting at the White House with a delegation of Christian religious leaders from the Middle East. They discussed the challenges faced by Christians in the region due to the rise of extremism. The President reaffirmed the commitment of the United States to counter the threat posed by ISIL and other terrorist groups in Iraq, Syria, Lebanon, and the broader Middle East. He emphasized the need for regional leaders to reject violence, promote moderation and tolerance, and end sectarian divisions. The President also acknowledged the historic role of Christian communities in the region and the importance of protecting religious minorities.